COMIC book writer <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Millar" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Millar" target="_blank">Mark Millar</a>'s <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Company" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Company" target="_blank">company</a> has raked in almost &pound2 million after his <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Working_%28musical%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Working_%28musical%29" target="_blank">work</a> was turned into <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood" target="_blank">Hollywood</a> blockbustersThe <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_people" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_people" target="_blank">Scot</a> has had a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/String_instrument" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/String_instrument" target="_blank">string</a> of <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Box_office" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Box_office" target="_blank">box office</a> successes including <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wanted_%282008_film%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wanted_%282008_film%29" target="_blank">Wanted</a> and the KickAss <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/24_%28TV_series%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/24_%28TV_series%29" target="_blank">series</a> after his creations were picked up by <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Film" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Film" target="_blank">movie</a> bossesHis <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Career" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Career" target="_blank">career</a> has taken off since he started <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Writing" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Writing" target="_blank">writing</a> as a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poverty" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poverty" target="_blank">penniless</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Student" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Student" target="_blank">student</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha_Stewart_Living" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha_Stewart_Living" target="_blank">living</a> in a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apartment" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apartment" target="_blank">flat</a> near his home <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Town_%282010_film%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Town_%282010_film%29" target="_blank">town</a> of <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coatbridge" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coatbridge" target="_blank">Coatbridge</a> LanarkshireAccounts recently <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Publishing" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Publishing" target="_blank">published</a> by his <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Business" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Business" target="_blank">firm</a> Millarworld <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_company" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_company" target="_blank">Limited</a> show it has <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asset" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asset" target="_blank">total assets</a> of &pound1815000Millar 45 set up the Glasgowbased <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Company" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Company" target="_blank">company</a> to have <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tinker,_Tailor,_Soldier,_Spy" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tinker,_Tailor,_Soldier,_Spy" target="_blank">control</a> over his own <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comic_book" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comic_book" target="_blank">comic book</a> charactersThe accounts show that <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Company" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Company" target="_blank">company</a> made profits of &pound364387 over the last <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/University" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/University" target="_blank">year</a> and owes &pound1592629 to unnamed creditorsIn recent <a href="http://dbpedia.org/re